My nursing career has taken me in so many directions over the years. This past month the opportunities I have had I could have never imagined while in nursing school @youngstownstate . I am entering my 17th year working in medicine as an RN and I am always honored to learn from the best. Yesterday I had the honor to volunteer with @dr.onury with @rockmedicine_ at Rolling Loud. It had been so long since my ER days and his staff was so amazing guiding me the whole way. 
This past weekend I was honored to be featured in @laweekly as one of the top injectors behind LA’s beauty scene and coming up in May I will be heading to Cameroon Africa to assist in Reconstructive Surgeries with some of the most prestigious Doctors i know @drmichaelkobeng ❤️ Sometimes the end of a chapter in life can lead you to a better story and I definitely think i have entered a happy ending

As an Aesthetic Nurse radiofrequency MicroNeedling is my absolute favorite procedure. I have been working with @cynosurelasers for 4 years now and was so excited to attend their beautiful event for Potenza. 
.
.

Potenza takes Radio Frequency microneedling to new levels through the number of customization options available. These options allow Potenza to treat all skin types, anywhere on the body, any time of the year.

The RF energy heats the underlying layers, causing constriction and tightening of the skin through soft-tissue coagulation, as well as causing the stimulation of collagen and elastin production. Because the RF energy is delivered so deeply, it can produce faster, more dramatic
results! DM me to book your treatments now 😘

This week I went on one of the most amazing journeys of my life. I had the honor to work with some of the most amazing medical professionals in Cameroon Africa to provide reconstructive surgery for free with @restoreworldwide and @asaf_cameroon . We worked endless hours to complete over 231 surgeries you can check out more from our mission in my highlights. If you would like to donate to our future missions, you can click on the link in my profile. 🙏

Turkey 🇹🇷 definitely did not disappoint. I used my missed connection to explore this beautiful country 💥 Although I missed mothers day, i was grateful for the opportunity to try something new - Can’t wait to go back
